00:13:39.290 --> 00:13:42.470
that we did for the launch
of Fastlane Road to Revenge.

00:13:42.470 --> 00:13:44.180
And through that,
hopefully, show you

00:13:44.180 --> 00:13:48.210
how we think about influences
and why we do what we do.

00:13:48.210 --> 00:13:50.990
So we think of ourselves as
a community-first developer.

00:13:50.990 --> 00:13:52.910
We think that a lot
of our big breaks

00:13:52.910 --> 00:13:55.040
came from genuinely
listening to our players

00:13:55.040 --> 00:13:58.190
and allowing them to inform
how we make our games

00:13:58.190 --> 00:14:00.480
and how we develop our games.

00:14:00.480 --> 00:14:03.320
We found that by involving
top players and influencers

00:14:03.320 --> 00:14:07.160
from the very, very, very
early stage of development--

00:14:07.160 --> 00:14:09.350
when I mean early stage,
I mean, very early

00:14:09.350 --> 00:14:10.730
in the the development.

00:14:10.730 --> 00:14:14.090
The game is not nearly as
polished or anything like that.

00:14:14.090 --> 00:14:16.190
But we find that
by doing that, they

00:14:16.190 --> 00:14:18.020
helped us understand
what would make

00:14:18.020 --> 00:14:20.229
the game interesting
for their communities.

00:14:20.229 --> 00:14:21.770
And then they became
our ambassadors.

00:14:21.770 --> 00:14:25.490
So we really kind of realized
that we're on to something--

00:14:25.490 --> 00:14:28.380
some really strong
marketing tool here.

00:14:28.380 --> 00:14:32.570
So we ended up going and using
this in every single game

00:14:32.570 --> 00:14:34.070
launch that we've had since.

00:14:34.070 --> 00:14:37.190
To give you some example,
for Rival Kingdoms,

00:14:37.190 --> 00:14:39.920
we were working on some big
innovations in build-in battle

00:14:39.920 --> 00:14:40.600
genre.

00:14:40.600 --> 00:14:43.280
So we needed a live community
to feedback on everything

00:14:43.280 --> 00:14:44.270
that we were doing.

00:14:44.270 --> 00:14:49.460
We recruited about 100 top
players and gaming influencers

00:14:49.460 --> 00:14:50.420
to do that for us.

00:14:50.420 --> 00:14:52.430
And they helped us
really shape the game.

00:14:52.430 --> 00:14:54.320
For Transformers Earth
Wars, for instance, we

00:14:54.320 --> 00:14:57.710
involved some big fan sites
and some gaming influencers,

00:14:57.710 --> 00:14:59.636
and they helped us do
all of the onboarding

00:14:59.636 --> 00:15:01.010
process into the
game, and really

00:15:01.010 --> 00:15:05.190
bridge between those fans of the
IP and the built-in battle play

00:15:05.190 --> 00:15:07.410
genre.

00:15:07.410 --> 00:15:11.640
But it became harder and harder
to reach those big influencers.

00:15:11.640 --> 00:15:14.850
And all the interactions
were becoming

00:15:14.850 --> 00:15:16.710
very much transactional based.

00:15:16.710 --> 00:15:19.210
We did a few of these for the
launch of Transformers Earth

00:15:19.210 --> 00:15:23.440
Wars, and actually did
paid content for that.

00:15:23.440 --> 00:15:25.667
But what we found is when
someone was making videos

00:15:25.667 --> 00:15:27.750
that they weren't really
passionate about the game

00:15:27.750 --> 00:15:31.090
that they were promoting,
it had two main problems.

00:15:31.090 --> 00:15:33.010
One, it didn't
drive any results.

00:15:33.010 --> 00:15:35.250
So it didn't really
justify us doing it again.

00:15:35.250 --> 00:15:37.860
And two, their community
picked up on the fact

00:15:37.860 --> 00:15:39.300
that they're not being genuine.

00:15:39.300 --> 00:15:40.950
And so they were
losing credibility.

00:15:40.950 --> 00:15:43.260
So in our opinion, this
isn't a sustainable way

00:15:43.260 --> 00:15:45.330
of doing things.

00:15:45.330 --> 00:15:48.210
Rather, we think
that content creation

00:15:48.210 --> 00:15:51.390
should be a product of a
meaningful relationship that

00:15:51.390 --> 00:15:52.950
really offers
something genuinely

00:15:52.950 --> 00:15:55.200
interesting for the
influencer, without asking

00:15:55.200 --> 00:15:56.700
for anything in return.

00:15:56.700 --> 00:15:58.410
They have to work
really hard these days

00:15:58.410 --> 00:16:01.530
to keep their channels engaged,
to keep their channels growing,

00:16:01.530 --> 00:16:04.147
to provide their fans
reasons to come back again

00:16:04.147 --> 00:16:04.980
and again and again.

00:16:04.980 --> 00:16:07.560
And we have to be a lot
more creative these days,

00:16:07.560 --> 00:16:10.310
and think right from
the start of things

00:16:10.310 --> 00:16:13.230
that would create that
inherent interest for them.

00:16:13.230 --> 00:16:14.730
Paul was talking
